cyclone.name: LAURA
cyclone.current_location: about 130 miles (210 km) southeast of San Juan, Puerto Rico
cyclone.trajectory: moving west-northwest across the Greater Antilles this weekend, then forecast to enter the Gulf of Mexico and curve northwest toward the central-western U.S. Gulf Coast
cyclone.expected_landfall_location: U.S. Gulf Coast (most likely Louisiana or far SE Texas)

weather_observation.warning_coast: Puerto Rico and nearby islands, U.S./British Virgin Islands, northern and southern coasts of the Dominican Republic, northern Haiti, southeastern Bahamas and Turks & Caicos
weather_observation.impacted_coast: Northern Leeward Islands, Virgin Islands, Puerto Rico, Hispaniola, eastern Cuba, southeastern Bahamas, Turks & Caicos, eventually the northern Gulf Coast
